I have been to Sidneys a few times and have always had a good time. I always see a new face behind the bar but the bartenders are usually friendly but tonight around 9:00 PM on 9/30/18 I came in with two other friends (also local bartenders) who wanted to celebrate a Saints win by doing a mind eraser shot between the three of us. (Take a pint glass, fill it to the top with ice, 1 shot of khalua, 1 shot of vodka and fill the rest of the glass with soda water) The bartender told us she refused to make the shot because it was "too intense" LOL When we even tried to explain it to her nicely, she simply refused to make it and laughed. It was very bizarre! You missed out on good tipping and easy pleasing patrons lady!
Nice hangout spot

First of all, just so we're clear, I visited Sidney's because I was attending a wedding. The bride was lovely, the groom non-existent, so we all ended up taking his place and I got to kiss the bride, so... 5 stars.  Also, it's your classic NOLA dive. Multiple local beers on tap, including Irish Channel Stout, to make the visits worthwhile.. A cute little chick from Lafayette, desperate for attention and tequila shots, to make the visits really worthwhile for the single woman or man. A nice dance floor and an overworked bar tender, to keep you wondering, was present, though I believe he didn't get a moment to kiss the bride, round the while thing out.. Well worth the visit.  The DJ was good, too.

Stumbled across this lovely little bar whilst taking a walk through the city. The prices are good, the bartender was friendly and knowledgeable. The day we went they were having a crawfish boil, which smelled delicious! This bar feels like you should be a regular here, it has a nice homey feel to it.  I would definitely come here again and sample some of their amazing beer selection.
Your local dive with mellow good vibes, a sweet and snarky staff and good beer selection. Sidney's mixes it up with great music, pop-up food events and  dance parties. Nice outdoor space as well.

Sidney's is ah-mazing.  The bartender named Jenelle will keep your thirst quenched with a smile on her face! The bar has an upbeat atmosphere - patrons are genuinly happy to be here. And they have fun events like a FREE CRAWFISH BOIL! (It was my first time, but man, it was great!)  The frozen coffee drink is life. It will keep you going while you get white girl wasted. **Quite literally- it tastes like a Starbucks Frappe**  I can't wait for my next trip down to NOLA. Sidney's will definitely be on my list!
